text: Welcome to the highly sought-after Stonebridge Oaks community! This stunning two-story home blends elegance, comfort, and functionality in a thoughtful split-bedroom layout designed for modern living. Soaring ceilings and abundant natural light fill the main living areas, creating an inviting and open atmosphere. The chef-inspired kitchen is the heart of the home, featuring quartz countertops, stainless steel appliances, a custom-wrapped island, stylish backsplash, and sleek lighting, perfect for everyday living and entertaining. Engineered hardwood floors, fresh paint, and updated fixtures add a polished, move-in-ready touch. Two fireplaces, one in the living room and one on the screened-in, covered patio, offer cozy settings year-round. The outdoor space extends your living area with room to relax, entertain, or enjoy a peaceful evening. The expansive primary suite on the main floor serves as a private retreat with a spa-like bath, soaking tub, separate shower, dual sinks with vanity, and a generous walk-in closet. An additional downstairs bedroom provides flexibility for guests or a home office. Upstairs, two well-appointed bedrooms are complemented by a versatile flex roomideal as a game room, media room, or second living space. Stonebridge Oaks offers more than a home, its a community. Residents enjoy a private clubhouse, resort-style pool, fitness center, and scenic walking trails. The HOA covers front-yard landscaping, sprinklers for front and backyard, and exterior upkeep of the home for a low-maintenance lifestyle. Seller will cover HOA dues through 2027 with acceptable offer. Ideally located just minutes from Downtown Grapevine, Southlake Town Square, and DFW International Airport, this home delivers beauty, convenience, and connection. Dont miss your opportunity to experience it all, schedule your tour today!

Worth and the The Grapevine Vintage RR with special excursions including the Stockyards and the Christmas Train. This sought after Bordeaux Residence is one of the larger Residences with 4 stories, 3 bdrm, 3.5 bath, 2 car garage and a 4th floor rooftop patio. This home also features two dedicated parking spots in front of the garage, extra storage under the stairs and two laundry rooms. The homes are built elevator ready and buyers have option to install after closing. Enjoy a front row seat to many of the special events Grapevine offers including Main St Days, Grapefest, and all that comes with being The Christmas Capital of Texas. Residences pictured are representative of Phase 2 homes which are under construction and estimated to be completed 3rd qtr of 2026.

Contemporary custom 2-story home situated on one of the largest lots in Western Oaks subdivision (0.848 acres). This spacious updated home offers 4 bedrooms, 3.5 bathrooms, and multiple living and entertaining areas. Grand double-door entry welcomes you into a soaring 2-story foyer and oversized living room flooded with natural light. Entertain with ease in formal dining room with vaulted ceiling or inviting family room featuring built-ins cabinets, shelves and fireplace. The kitchen boasts granite countertops, island with sink, workstation, double ovens, microwave, and 4-burner gas cooktop. Utility room has pocket-door, cabinets, sink, built-in ironing board and cabinets. Freshly painted interior and carpet installed in July 2025, as well as, updated secondary bathrooms. First-floor private primary suite showcases a tray ceiling, recessed lighting, and wood-look tile flooring that continues into the remodeled ensuite bath and closet. Spa-like bathroom features skylight, heated floors, soaking tub, frameless river rock shower, ceiling fan, and dual vanities while the walk-in closet includes a built-in ironing board and chest of drawers. Upstairs, three spacious bedrooms, one with cedar closet, another with pocket-door, Jack-and-Jill bath, an additional full bath, and a large game room with a raised ceiling, wet bar with bar seating, wine fridge & rack, and built-insplus a walk-out balcony overlooking the greenbelt. The 4th bedroom includes built-in cabinets and shelves with a desk area, making it ideal for a private office or guest suite. Additional highlights include an intercom system, central vacuum, 3-car garage configured with a 2-car bay and a separate single-car bay, all windows have a lifetime transferable warranty, plus a composition, hail-resistant Class IV roof (installed July 2025). Backs to green space and creek. Upper yard approx. 49 patio to retaining wall and 84 wideideal for pool. Clear lower brush to expand entertainment area and view of creek.

text: Live your best life in one of the most desirable homes in Historic Grapevine, located on a leafy residential street surrounded by exquisite examples of classic architecture. A truly walkable lifestyle just steps to Main Street, Hotel Vin, the historic train station, and the dining, shopping and live music that make this charming city so unique. The historically significant home was built in 1940 by former Grapevine Mayor William Floyd Deacon. A thorough and award winning renovation was completed in 2015, preserving all of the history and charm and adding sophisticated modern livability. Sumptuous Bianco Venatino marble, Wolf commercial range, brilliant floor to ceiling windows, gleaming wood floors, and a spacious open floor plan make this home as functional as it is beautiful. Situated on a generous third-acre lot with a stunning 2021 pool, spa, outdoor kitchen and screened in porch, the outdoor living space is a perfect backdrop for the Gatsby lifestyle with croquet and badminton on the expansive lawn, and homemade ice cream and rummy on the romantic screened in porch complete with fireplace. The dramatic dining room has walls of windows bringing the outdoors in for the most intimate and memorable dinner parties. When the sun goes down repair to the spacious rooftop terrace nestled in the tree tops. Join your neighbors on the lawn for the annual Christmas parade that goes right down the street. DFW Airport is just minutes away and the train to downtown Forth Worth is just a short stroll down the street. Glamorous marble-clad primary suite has soaking tub, dual vanities, oversized shower and walk in closet. Each of the three additional beds and baths are equally beautiful with their own unique style. Designer tile & lighting throughout. Energy efficient: Spray foam, dual tankless water heaters, dual zone ACs & LED throughout. The spacious lot has plenty of room to add a larger garage if desired, as the neighbors on either side have done. This home has it all!

text: Welcome to this wonderfully custom 2017 home nestled on a tranquil, wooded 0.936-acre lot. Just minutes from the shopping, dining, & vibrant events of Historic Downtown Grapevine. With no HOA restrictions & located outside the historic zone, it provides both freedom & charm in a highly desirable area. The home offers approximately 2, 743sqft of interior living space. Rich hardwood floors run throughout the home, complementing the warm tones & custom wood cabinetry found in every room. The open-concept living area features the homes 2 fireplaces, creating an inviting space for gatherings & relaxation. Off the main living is a dedicated office enclosed by a pair of antique leaded glass doors, with custom built-in drawers & shelving. The heart of the home is the chefs kitchen, thoughtfully designed with 2 large islands, a built-in refrigerator seamlessly integrated with cabinet fronts, a full-size dishwasher, & 2 additional dishwasher drawers also concealed with cabinetry. The home offers 3 beds & 3 full baths. One secondary bedroom features an ensuite bath with a roll-in shower, providing ADA-friendly accessibility without compromising style. The spacious primary suite includes a luxurious bathroom with a large walk-in shower, space for a freestanding tub, & double vanities. The oversized walk-in closet offers extensive storage & conveniently opens into the utility room containing a Texas Tech-engineered storm shelter. Features an impressive 1, 200sqft covered outdoor living area, equipped with a full bath, built-in grill & prep station, & a large stone fireplace. This overlooks a beautifully landscaped backyard complete with raised beds, fruit trees, a fire pit, & plenty of space for entertaining. This home is a rare find, offering timeless design, custom finishes, & a lifestyle that perfectly balances serene living with access to the very best of Grapevine. Dont miss your opportunity to make this extraordinary property your new home.

text: Bring All Offers! Own a piece of Historic Downtown Grapevine! This Tri-plex is within walking distance of Grapevines renowned restaurants, shops, wineries, and more. Each unit features 2 bedrooms, 1 full bath, a kitchen, and spacious living and dining areas. Outside, you'll find 6 parking spaces, a community laundry area, and a large fenced backyard. All units but 1 (we are getting it ready to be leased) are currently leased and ready for you to take over!

Price Improvement LAKE Lifestyle at its BEST! This home includes your own designated BOAT SLIP at the private community boat dock - a luxury that rarely comes available in this neighborhood. Take morning and evening walks along the lake through Bear Lake Trail and Lakeview Park. This well-maintained brick home sits on a quiet, corner lot with mature trees. Recent updates include a complete kitchen remodel in 2023, featuring abundant custom cabinetry with pull-out shelves and a lazy susan, a built-in SubZero refrigerator with custom panels, 6-burner Dacor gas range with double ovens, Bosch dishwasher, built-in microwave drawer, and built-in wine refrigerator. Large walk-in pantry. The primary bedroom is spacious and features a large sitting area for reading and relaxing, or an ideal space for your personal gym equipment. The primary bathroom offers dual vanities with travertine counters, jetted tub, steam shower, and custom closet built-ins. The windows are appointed with custom wood shutters in both the front and the back of the home. The formal dining room flows effortlessly into two living areas, perfect for entertaining family and friends. Generous great room with fireplace and wet bar, offering flexibility for styling it as a living room or a game room. Off the great room are two upstairs bedrooms and a full bathroom. Just 10 minutes to historic downtown Grapevine and iconic Southlake Town Square, and less than 10 miles to Dallas-Fort Worth International Airport. This unique location is just steps from the lake, minutes from great shopping and amazing restaurants, but feels worlds away from all the hustle and bustle. We invite you to tour this beautifully updated home in Grapevine Lake Estates.

text: Welcome to this tastefully updated 3-bedroom, 2-bath traditional home that perfectly blends comfort, style, and functionality. Nestled in a quiet, established neighborhood, this inviting residence offers generous living spaces and timeless charm throughout. With a newly installed roof, extensive durable and attractive wood-look tile, and neutral colors, this one-story home offers modern conveniences with classic touches. Step inside to find a large formal living room ideal for gatherings, a cozy family room with abundant natural light, and a beautiful formal dining area that makes entertaining a breeze. The heart of the home features a well-appointed kitchen with ample cabinetry, granite counter space, gleaming stainless appliances, and a convenient breakfast nook. The spacious primary suite is located at the back of the home and features a neutral bathroom with custom tile work, an extended shower and garden tub, and generous walk-in closet. Conveniently located near desirable schools, Bear Creek Park and dog park, walking and biking trails, nearby community pool, shopping, and entertainment, this home also offers easy highway access for a quick commute to work or DFW airport. Despite being a voluntary HOA, the neighborhood is active and offers several events throughout the year for anyone looking to plug in and foster a sense of community. This stunning 2, 576-square-foot residence, located in the coveted Grapevine, TX, offers the perfect balance of luxury and versatility. Currently a one-story home, it also offers the option to be transformed into a two-story masterpiece, allowing you to customize it to fit your unique vision. From the moment you step through the grand front door, youll be greeted by a space filled with natural light, thanks to an abundance of large windows throughout the home. The open floor plan features three spacious bedrooms and two and a half bathrooms, all adorned with premium finishes, including marble countertops in the bathrooms and sleek quartz countertops in the kitchen. Delta fixtures and LED dimmable light switches add a touch of modern elegance to every room. The heart of the home is the open-concept living area, where a 3-pane sliding back door seamlessly connects the indoors to the outdoor patio. Imagine enjoying serene evenings by the appliance fireplace, which is conveniently activated with the flip of a light switch, creating a cozy atmosphere thats perfect for relaxation. For the aspiring chef, the kitchen boasts gas appliances, ample storage, and a beautiful expanse of quartz countertops, making it a perfect space for preparing meals or entertaining guests. The pristine white cabinets create a timeless look that complements the homes sophisticated style. This home also offers a 3-car garage with a smart garage door opener, ensuring convenience and security. A 30-year shingle roof provides durability and peace of mind for years to come. Located near the tranquil beauty of Grapevine Lake, this home is the perfect setting to enjoy both luxurious living and natural surroundings. Dont miss the opportunity to make this exceptional home yours where luxury, comfort, and endless possibilities await.

Beautiful 4 bedroom, 2.5 bathroom home within walking distance to Dove elementary and Grapevine Lake. Home has new flooring, granite counter tops, new modern light fixtures, fresh paint, blinds, etc. Main living areas are downstairs with living room, dining room, kitchen, half bath, laundry and a multipurpose room currently used as a mud room and office space. The backyard has a nice deck for entertainment and a small yard space for a pet. This home is in a wonderful location close to downtown Grapevine, shopping, entertainment and a quick trip to DFW airport or enjoy an evening walk to Dove Park. Perfect for first time home buyers or investors. Come take a look!

text: Tucked at the end of a peaceful cul-de-sac, just a short walk from the shimmering shores of Lake Grapevine, stands a two-story home thats been loved, lived in, and carefully maintained since 1986. As you step through the front door, you're welcomed into a warm and inviting living room with soaring cathedral ceilings. A floor-to-ceiling brick fireplace anchors the space, enveloped by a wall of built-in bookcases. Overhead, a modern wagon wheel LED chandelier adds a touch of rustic elegance. The heart of the home is the kitchen, where morning coffee is shared at the eat-in nook and holiday meals are prepared for family and friends. Just beyond, theres a separate formal dining room, perfect for gatherings both big and small. Nearby, a spacious laundry room with extra storage and a convenient half bath make daily living easy. Upstairs, all three bedrooms are thoughtfully arranged for privacy and comfort. The primary suite offers its own en-suite bathroom, while two more bedrooms share a second full bath. Whether it's the laughter of children, the quiet hum of a home office, or the peace of a restful night's sleepthis upper level is ready for whatever life brings. Out back, a simple fenced yard and deck provide just enough space to enjoy the outdoorsno pool to maintain. Its the kind of yard where you can sip iced tea on a summer afternoon, grill on weekends, or let the dog run free. This all-electric home runs on city utilities, with upgraded security and fire alarm wiring in place (updated in early 2023). New carpet and luxury vinyl tile, installed in April 2023, Major items replaced since 2022 that include AC, Heat Pump, Hot Water Tank. Exterior professionally painted 4-24 with Sherwin Williams Paints and a 2019 Roof replacement add comfort and freshness throughout. So if you're looking for more than square footageif you're looking for a home with heart, history, and a future waiting to be writtenthis may be the one.

text: NEW Construction! The Grapevine Brownstones Phase 2 present a limited opportunity to own a luxury Lock and Leave Residence on Dallas Rd in the heart of Grapevine, across from Hotel Vin, steps from Historic Main St, Peace Plaza, Harvest Hall and The Grapevine REC. A short walk across Dallas Rd to the TEX Rail which will drop you at DFW Airport or Ft. Worth and the The Grapevine Vintage RR with special excursions including the Stockyards and the Christmas Train. This beautiful corner Residence, the Marquis, is white brick, and represents one of a few remaining homes that front Dallas Rd, has 4 stories with 3 bdrm, 3.5 bath, 2 car garage and the 4th floor rooftop enclosed living area. Features include 12 foot ceilings in the kitchen and living room, bay window in the 1st floor bedroom and kitchen, and the fourth floor enclosed Terrace room with a wetbar. These homes are built elevator ready which buyer can choose to add after closing. Enjoy a front row seat to many of the special events Grapevine offers including Main St Fest, Grapefest, and all that comes with being The Christmas Capital of Texas. Walking is easy with a 75 Walkscore and also quick access to highways, Southlake Town Square, and DFW Airport. Expected completion dates are 2nd quarter of 2026. All pictures and plans are representations of Phase 2 Residences.

Pedestrian living at it's finest! This freshly updated Austin Stone 4 bedroom home features a luxurious and relaxing outdoor living space with a sterling waterfall pool and spa, cabana with sitting area, dining space and a very large grassy green lawn area. Located just a stone's throw away from Historic Downtown Grapevine which is lined with restaurants, galleries and shops makes these two worlds collide. Interiors showcase an open floor plan with views through the home, an updated and chic kitchen with stainless farm sink, ss appliances, white granite countertops and oversized subway tile backsplash and modernized ensuite primary bedroom. 4th bedroom can dual as a second living room or home office. See List of Updates from 2021. Highlights include: new roof, Lennox HVAC, replaced siding on the entire back wall of home, heavy Iron exterior doors, swimming pool with heated spa and Pentar Pool equipment, outdoor lighting. Conveniently located to Dallas Fort Worth International Airport, Downtown Grapevine, Highway 114 and a myriad of DFW's sports and entertainment arenas.

text: Tucked away in the coveted Westover neighborhood, this stunning 5-bedroom, 4-bathroom home brings space, style, and comfort together in perfect harmony. Sitting proudly on a quiet cul-de-sac, the curb appeal draws you inand the interior seals the deal. Step inside to find rich handscraped wood floors that flow seamlessly through the open floorplan, setting a warm and upscale tone. Natural light pours in from every angle, highlighting the multiple spacious living areas designed for both entertaining and everyday comfort. Whether you're hosting a lively dinner party or enjoying a quiet movie night, theres room for it all. The heart of the home features a generous living space anchored by a cozy gas fireplace, perfect for those cooler Texas evenings. The kitchen connects effortlessly to both the formal and casual dining areas, offering ample cabinetry, granite counter space, breakfast bar, and a layout that makes cooking feel like a joynot a chore. The primary suite is conveniently located on the ground floor, offering privacy and ease with an oversized bedroom, large walk-in closet, and a spa-like bath retreat. Upstairs, the secondary bedrooms are equally spacious, with flexible options for a home office, media room, or playroomwhatever fits your lifestyle. Out back, the peaceful cul-de-sac location means added privacy and minimal traffic, making the backyard the perfect setting for morning coffee or evening barbecues. text: Willow Wood Horse Farm is without a doubt one of the finest examples of modern architecture combined with an equestrian lifestyle on 9.753+/- acres. The residence was originally designed by Lou Simmons, who collaborated with Bob Sullivan on the project to help it come into completion. Situated in the heart of the Dallas-Fort Worth Metroplex, just minutes from Lake Grapevine, Southlake, and an easy commute to DFW International Airport, this property affords someone the ability to have all the comforts of the city, while living just slightly removed from it all. The main residence and equestrian facilities are immaculate and ready for the next generation of ownership. This property is a must have for the individual desiring to be close to the city but enjoy a more peaceful and country-like setting. Improvements: This custom designed home was completed in 2022 and is truly an example of elegance. The 4, 353 SF home demands attention as it sits on the highest point of the property. Hear the rumble of your tires on the cobble stone drive as you approach the house and take in the modern architectural masterpiece that awaits. Situated on either side of the main door of the home is a beautifully understated Koi pond that welcomes visitors before entering through the massive glass door and entry way. The home is constructed of insulated concrete form (ICF) with steal joists and a deck roof system. Walls and windows of the home provide superior thermal and sound insulation. After walking through the threshold, you will notice a grand view all the way through the living areas of the house, overlooking the 3, 000 SF IPE back deck, 80 ft long salt water swimming pool, through the pasture to the equestrian facilities. The welcoming views are complimented by a very warm and luxurious open-concept living space that combines the living room, kitchen, and dining areas. Custom quarter sawn walnut millworker can be found throughout the kitchen and living areas as well as the rest of the residence. The kitchen is ideal for the master chef with Gagneau appliances including a steam convection oven, a conventional convection oven, coffee machine, cooktop, dishwasher, separate paneled refrigerator and freezer units, as well as a warming drawer. Just off the kitchen is a half bath and a full butlers pantry with prep space and a full-size dishwasher. Each of the bedrooms has a unique and different view of the property. The primary bedroom features similar views to the main living area, a spacious walk-in closet, a bathroom with solid stone bath tub and wash basins by Piet Boone, and Donrbracht platinum plumbing fixtures. The two additional bedrooms have on suite bathrooms also with Donrbracht fixtures and excellent clothing storage for family or guests. All main rooms have Italian pocket door hardware with soft open/close features and are fully sealed with gaskets to aid in sound transfer between rooms when doors are closed. Journeying up and down the custom-built metal framed staircase is an artistic treat in itself. Going up the stairs to the second floor viewing area re-emphasizes the stunning views of the grounds and surrounding area, complete with a dishwasher, fridge/freezer/icemaker, a dumbwaiter, and floor to ceiling windows and doors that open to a covered porch and roof top IPE deck. The lower level of the home features an acoustically balanced theater with Dynaudio speakers and sound system designed by Ember Audio to provide a true movie theater experience from the comfort of your own home. The theatre is complete with a 250-bottle wine cooler, 8 ft concert walls, and a powder bath. All of which could also be used as a very nice storm cellar.

text: Come see this beautiful Grapevine home. It is located on a large lot and quiet cul-de-sac with so many majestic tall oak trees. So much character everywhere you look! Inside are two spacious living rooms, BOTH with a fireplace, and two dining areas on either side of the kitchen, both with large bay windows, providing an abundance of natural light throughout the house. It can also be a wonderful multi-gen living space, teen apartment, a man-cave or she-chateau. Endless possibilities! Easy access to major highways, DFW Airport, Parr Park, shopping and restaurants. text: Located just minutes to the boat launches at Grapevine Lake, this home can house your boat, toys, workshop, workout room, or the collection of cars of every hobbyist's dream! Check out the 4+ car barn with HVAC! With walkability to downtown Grapevine to the restaurants, shops, and wineries, you're sure to love this location! This historical home, known as the GE Hunt Home, was originally constructed in 1910 and rebuilt in 2016 through a meticulous renovation that preserved its soul while anchoring it in the now. Set on a lush half-acre lot filled with mature native trees, this home feels like a page out of Grapevines past with a future-proof foundation, literally built atop a modern steel pier-and-beam system. With over 4, 500 square feet under roof and 2, 780 square feet in the main home, the layout is as thoughtful as it is functional. Downstairs, the primary suite offers privacy and comfort with a spa-like ensuite bath, while a guest suite on the same floor provides hospitality with ease. A light-filled great room flows into the heart of the homea luxurious kitchen with Thermador appliances and era-inspired cabinetry and color, plus and a dining area designed for gathering. Upstairs, two additional bedrooms each feature full baths, accompanied by a second living area and an expansive office space that could double as a creative studio or library. The details tell the real story with preserved trimwork, hardwood floors, and antique-inspired fixtures which are all balanced by smart updates and energy-efficient systems. Outside, a 975 sq ft detached garage-workshop echoes the aesthetic of a classic Texas barn, offering functionality with curb appeal. And the porte-cochere near the mudroom and laundry isnt just a design feature, its a daily convenience, enhanced by the Generac generator, ready on demand to power the home. This is more than a historical homeits a legacy, lovingly restored and ready for its next chapter.

text: Nestled in the heart of the vibrant city of Grapevine, this exceptional lot offers the perfect blend of location and convenience. Located downtown, one block from charming Historic Main Street, you'll have easy access to Grapevine's renowned shopping, dining, local wineries and entertainment options, as well as top-rated schools, parks and Grapevine Lake. Grapevine is a commuter's paradise, strategically located in the center of the Dallas-Fort Worth metroplex. With major highway access and home to DFW International Airport, this location offers unparalleled convenience. Additionally, Downtown Grapevine is a hub for the TexRail commuter train, connecting directly to DFW Airport in seven minutes, and providing commuters easy access from Fort Worth and cities in between. This accessibility makes it ideal for both business and residential development, offering immense potential for future growth. This 14, 923 sq. ft. lot is currently zoned Commercial, with potential for residential development after approval from Grapevine's Planning and Zoning. There is the possibility to subdivide the lot into two residential parcels, offering a rare opportunity to build one's dream home. Take advantage of the local wineries, scenic lake, and rich history that make Grapevine a unique and desirable destination. Don't let this rare opportunity pass you by-this property is waiting for you to make it your own! Buyer and Buyer Agent to verify all information required for development with the City of Grapevine.
